BEGIN:VEVENT
DESCRIPTION:<a href="https://tfl.gov.uk/tube-dlr-overground/status/?Input=&lineIds=&dateTypeSelect=Future%20date&direction=&startDate=2026-03-15T04:30:00&endDate=2026-03-15T07:45:00">Disruption map.</a>\n\nELIZABETH LINE: Sunday 15 March\, until 0745\, no service between Paddington and Ealing Broadway. Please use London Underground connections. The Saturday evening 2345 Didcot Parkway to London Paddington GWR train will finish its journey at Ealing Broadway. The Sunday morning 0638 London Paddington to Reading GWR train will start from Ealing Broadway and will run slightly later throughout. TfL Central line connections will be available between Central London and Ealing Broadway.
DTEND:20260315T074500Z
DTSTART:20260315T043000Z
SUMMARY:Elizabeth line: Part Closure
UID:e36f959d-9562-44fc-846f-900225783001@e36f.org
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
DESCRIPTION:<a href="https://tfl.gov.uk/tube-dlr-overground/status/?Input=&lineIds=&dateTypeSelect=Future%20date&direction=&startDate=2026-03-22T07:45:00&endDate=2026-03-23T01:29:00">Disruption map.</a>\n\nELIZABETH LINE: Sunday 22 March\, from 0745\, a reduced service operates between Paddington National Rail station and Maidenhead / Heathrow. Two trains an hour serve Acton Main Line\, Hanwell\, Heathrow Terminal 4\, Heathrow Terminal 5\, West Drayton\, Langley\, Slough\, Burnham and Maidenhead. Four trains an hour serve West Ealing and Heathrow Terminals 2 & 3. Six trains an hour serve Ealing Broadway\, Southall and Hayes & Harlington.
DTEND:20260323T012900Z
DTSTART:20260322T074500Z
SUMMARY:Elizabeth line: Reduced Service
UID:f60565c7-c998-4974-8ef7-3943f64c907c@f605.org
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
DESCRIPTION:<a href="https://tfl.gov.uk/tube-dlr-overground/status/?Input=&lineIds=&dateTypeSelect=Future%20date&direction=&startDate=2026-05-04T22:00:00&endDate=2026-05-04T22:59:00">Disruption map.</a>\n\nELIZABETH LINE: Monday 4\, Tuesday 5\, Wednesday 6 and Thursday 7 May\, the 2217 Abbey Wood to Reading train will terminate at Maidenhead. Customers travelling to Twyford and Reading should change at Maidenhead to the 2338 GWR service to Twyford and Reading. At Maidenhead\, connecting westbound GWR trains to Twyford and Reading use Platform 1. For step-free interchange from platform 3 to platform 1\, please use the lift to the main entrance\, and then continue at street level under the railway bridge and up Shoppenhangers Road to the car park. Please ask staff to open the gate to platform 1\, and allow extra time for your journey
DTEND:20260504T225900Z
DTSTART:20260504T220000Z
SUMMARY:Elizabeth line: Reduced Service
UID:092043f0-3fdb-438e-a17f-d20b752fc36d@0920.org
